Police officers from the Rapid Rail Police Unit recovered stolen copper cables and other cables from a scrap yard in New Germany near Pinetown, in KwaZulu-Natal on Wednesday and arrested a man. Kwazulu-Natal police spokesperson, Captain Nqobile Gwala said the unit was conducting operations in Pinetown when they received information about a scrap yard dealing in stolen copper cables. “The team proceeded to the identified scrap yard that is situated on Rawat Road in New Germany. Upon searching the premises, police discovered a hole in the yard. Inside the hole, police officers found copper cables which belong to Transnet, Prasa and the EThekwini Municipality hidden,” she said. She said police recovered 102kg of copper cables and 92 kg of other cables. A 27-year-old suspect was placed under arrest for possession of a stolen property and was due to appear in court in Pinetown, she added. The KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Commissioner, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula praised the team for the recovery of the copper cables. “We are appealing to community members to continue working hand in hand with the police in the fight against the theft of copper cables in our province,” he said.